  <prompt>
    Filed 2026-05-26 per operator mandate "must ensure these issues are resolved as part of this
    project (Phase 6)". Task 068 fixed the Jest+React 19 environment, unblocking 544 additional
    tests that had been silently skipped. 142 of those tests fail on test-content issues
    (userEvent quirks with RTL v16, themeStorage spy patterns broken by React 19 effect timing,
    etc.). These aren't bugs in production code — they're test-content quality issues that the
    React-16 + RTL-v14 pinning was hiding.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Test engineer fluent in RTL v16 + React 19 testing patterns. Bulk-pattern fixer.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `@spaarke/ui-components` test suite runs clean — 0 module-resolution errors, ≤10 test-content
    failures (down from 142). All R4-added tests (042 SprkChat.onAttachmentReady, 050 attachment
    boundaries) pass. Memo catalogs any deferred failures with rationale.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Baseline before R4: `Test Suites: 12 passed, 43 failed (392 tests passing)` — most failures
      were `Cannot find module 'react-dom/client'` (env-broken silently).
      After task 068: `Test Suites: 34 passed, 21 failed (936 tests passing)` — env fixed; 142
      test-content failures surfaced.

      Likely failure patterns (per task 068 memo + sub-agent observations):
      - userEvent API migrations (RTL v14 → v16; sync → async; `.click()` → `userEvent.click()`)
      - themeStorage spy patterns broken by React 19 effect timing (effects now batch differently)
      - act() warnings becoming hard failures
      - Snapshot drift from React 19 renderer output changes
      - Pre-existing skipped tests now executing + failing

      Per operator decision 2026-05-26: file as task 071 in R4 Phase 6, full triage + fix.
    </background>
